dlinkSwEntityExtMIB.name: dlinkSwEntityExtMIB

revisions.description: Add dEntityExtFactoryResetButton to support factory reset button trap.
This is the first version of this MIB.

dlinkSwEntityExtMIB.contactinfo: D-Link Corporation Postal: No. 289, Sinhu 3rd Rd., Neihu District, Taipei City 114, Taiwan, R.O.C Tel: +886-2-66000123 E-mail: tsd@dlink.com.tw
dlinkSwEntityExtMIB.description: This MIB module provides essential information about the system and defines the managed objects that support the monitoring of alarms generated by physical entities, including temperature sensors, fans and power supplies.

dEntityExtEnvTempTable.name: dEntityExtEnvTempTable
dEntityExtEnvTempTable.description: The table consists of a list of temperature information.

dEntityExtEnvTempEntry.name: dEntityExtEnvTempEntry
dEntityExtEnvTempEntry.description: An entry represents the temperature status of a testpoint.

dEntityExtEnvTempUnitId.name: dEntityExtEnvTempUnitId
dEntityExtEnvTempUnitId.description: This object indicates the unit (stacking device) or slot (chassis device) ID at which the testpoint is located.

dEntityExtEnvTempIndex.name: dEntityExtEnvTempIndex
dEntityExtEnvTempIndex.description: This object is used to uniquely identify the testpoint within a unit/slot. This index is for SNMP purposes only, and has no intrinsic meaning.

dEntityExtEnvTempDescr.name: dEntityExtEnvTempDescr
dEntityExtEnvTempDescr.description: This object provides human-sensible identification for the testpoint. e.g. 'Inlet', 'Center', 'Outlet'.

dEntityExtEnvTempCurrent.name: dEntityExtEnvTempCurrent
dEntityExtEnvTempCurrent.description: This object indicates the current measurement of the testpoint.

dEntityExtEnvTempThresholdLow.name: dEntityExtEnvTempThresholdLow
dEntityExtEnvTempThresholdLow.description: The object indicates the minimum acceptable reading of the testpoint in degrees Celsius.

dEntityExtEnvTempThresholdHigh.name: dEntityExtEnvTempThresholdHigh
dEntityExtEnvTempThresholdHigh.description: The object indicates the maximum acceptable reading of the testpoint in degrees Celsius.

dEntityExtEnvTempStatus.name: dEntityExtEnvTempStatus
dEntityExtEnvTempStatus.description: The object indicates the current temperature is over the thresholds or not. 'abnormal' indicates the temperature is over the thresholds. 'ok' indicates the temperature is not over the thresholds.

dEntityExtEnvFanTable.name: dEntityExtEnvFanTable
dEntityExtEnvFanTable.description: The table is used to display the status of fans.

dEntityExtEnvFanEntry.name: dEntityExtEnvFanEntry
dEntityExtEnvFanEntry.description: An entry represents a fan status.

dEntityExtEnvFanUnitId.name: dEntityExtEnvFanUnitId
dEntityExtEnvFanUnitId.description: This object indicates the unit (stacking device) or slot (chassis device) ID at which the fan is located.

dEntityExtEnvFanIndex.name: dEntityExtEnvFanIndex
dEntityExtEnvFanIndex.description: This object is used to uniquely identify the fan within a unit/slot. This index is for SNMP purposes only, and has no intrinsic meaning.

dEntityExtEnvFanDescr.name: dEntityExtEnvFanDescr
dEntityExtEnvFanDescr.description: This object provides human-sensible identification for the fan. e.g. 'Left 1' for the first fan on the left.

dEntityExtEnvFanStatus.name: dEntityExtEnvFanStatus
dEntityExtEnvFanStatus.description: This object indicates the fan status.

dEntityExtEnvPowerTable.name: dEntityExtEnvPowerTable
dEntityExtEnvPowerTable.description: The table is used to display the status of the power modules.

dEntityExtEnvPowerEntry.name: dEntityExtEnvPowerEntry
dEntityExtEnvPowerEntry.description: An entry contains the information of a power module.

dEntityExtEnvPowerUnitId.name: dEntityExtEnvPowerUnitId
dEntityExtEnvPowerUnitId.description: This object indicates the unit (stacking device) or slot (chassis device) ID at which the power module is located.

dEntityExtEnvPowerIndex.name: dEntityExtEnvPowerIndex
dEntityExtEnvPowerIndex.description: This object indicates the ID of the power module. This object is used to uniquely identify the power module. This index is for SNMP purposes only, and has no intrinsic meaning.

dEntityExtEnvPowerDescr.name: dEntityExtEnvPowerDescr
dEntityExtEnvPowerDescr.description: This object provides human-sensible information for the power module. e.g. '#1 (internal)', '#2 (external)'.

dEntityExtEnvPowerUsedPower.name: dEntityExtEnvPowerUsedPower
dEntityExtEnvPowerUsedPower.description: This object indicates the amount of the power that has been allocated.

dEntityExtEnvPowerMaxPower.name: dEntityExtEnvPowerMaxPower
dEntityExtEnvPowerMaxPower.description: This object indicates maximum power which the power module can supply.

dEntityExtEnvPowerStatus.name: dEntityExtEnvPowerStatus
dEntityExtEnvPowerStatus.description: This object indicates the status of the power.

dEntityExtEnvAirFlowTable.name: dEntityExtEnvAirFlowTable
dEntityExtEnvAirFlowTable.description: The table is used to display the status of the air flow function.

dEntityExtEnvAirFlowEntry.name: dEntityExtEnvAirFlowEntry
dEntityExtEnvAirFlowEntry.description: An entry contains the information of the air flow function.

dEntityExtEnvAirFlowUnitId.name: dEntityExtEnvAirFlowUnitId
dEntityExtEnvAirFlowUnitId.description: This object indicates the unit (stacking device) or slot (chassis device) ID at which the air flow module is located.

dEntityExtEnvAirFlowStatus.name: dEntityExtEnvAirFlowStatus
dEntityExtEnvAirFlowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of the air flow. The fans' air flow direction must match the system's air flow direction to form an integrated air flow. For example: In DXS-3600, the normal fans' air flow direction must match the power fan's air flow direction. The power fan blow the cold air from outside to inside, all the normal fans must blow the hot air from inside to outside. Or the power fan blow the hot air from inside to outside, all the normal fans must blow the cold air from outside to inside. If one or more fans' air flow direction does not match the system's air flow direction, it will form an abnormal air flow. Then this log message will be triggered. ok(1) : A recover event indicates the air flow back to normal. abnormal(2): An alarm event indicates the air flow detects abnormal.

dEntityExtEnvNotifyEnable.name: dEntityExtEnvNotifyEnable
dEntityExtEnvNotifyEnable.description: This object indicates whether a specified notification is enabled or not. If a bit corresponding to a notification is set to 1, then the specified notification can be generated. fan(0) - fan trap state for warning fan event (fan failed or fan recover). power(1) - power trap state for warning power event (power failure or power recovery). temperature(2) - temperature trap state for warning temperature event (temperature exceeds the thresholds or temperature recover).

dEntityExtUnitTable.name: dEntityExtUnitTable
dEntityExtUnitTable.description: The table is used to display information of units.

dEntityExtUnitEntry.name: dEntityExtUnitEntry
dEntityExtUnitEntry.description: An entry contains essential information of a unit.

dEntityExtUnitIndex.name: dEntityExtUnitIndex
dEntityExtUnitIndex.description: This object indicates the unit (stacking device) or slot (chassis device) ID.

dEntityExtUnitStatus.name: dEntityExtUnitStatus
dEntityExtUnitStatus.description: This object represents the status of the unit: ok(1) - This indicates the unit is okay. failed(2) - This indicates the unit fails due to some reason. empty(3) - This indicates that the unit is provisioned but currently not installed.

dEntityExtUnitUpTime.name: dEntityExtUnitUpTime
dEntityExtUnitUpTime.description: This object provides the up time in units of seconds for the unit since it was last re-initialized.

dEntityExtMemoryUtilTable.name: dEntityExtMemoryUtilTable
dEntityExtMemoryUtilTable.description: The table is used to display memory utilization information.

dEntityExtMemoryUtilEntry.name: dEntityExtMemoryUtilEntry
dEntityExtMemoryUtilEntry.description: An entry contains memory utilization information.

dEntityExtMemUtilUnitId.name: dEntityExtMemUtilUnitId
dEntityExtMemUtilUnitId.description: This object indicates the unit (stacking device) or slot (chassis device) ID.

dEntityExtMemUtilType.name: dEntityExtMemUtilType
dEntityExtMemUtilType.description: The object indicates the memory type of the entry.

dEntityExtMemUtilTotal.name: dEntityExtMemUtilTotal
dEntityExtMemUtilTotal.description: This object indicates the total memory size of the entry.

dEntityExtMemUtilUsed.name: dEntityExtMemUtilUsed
dEntityExtMemUtilUsed.description: This object indicates the used memory size of the entry.

dEntityExtMemUtilFree.name: dEntityExtMemUtilFree
dEntityExtMemUtilFree.description: This object indicates the free memory size of the entry.

dEntityExtCpuUtilTable.name: dEntityExtCpuUtilTable
dEntityExtCpuUtilTable.description: The table is used to display CPU utilization information.

dEntityExtCpuUtilUnitId.name: dEntityExtCpuUtilUnitId
dEntityExtCpuUtilUnitId.description: This object indicates the unit (stacking device) or slot (chassis device) ID.

dEntityExtCpuUtilCpuID.name: dEntityExtCpuUtilCpuID
dEntityExtCpuUtilCpuID.description: This object is used to uniquely identify the CPU within a unit (multiprocessing system).

dEntityExtCpuUtilFiveSeconds.name: dEntityExtCpuUtilFiveSeconds
dEntityExtCpuUtilFiveSeconds.description: This objects indicates the overall CPU busy percentage in the last 5 second period. The value will be between 0% (idle) and 100% (very busy).

dEntityExtCpuUtilOneMinute.name: dEntityExtCpuUtilOneMinute
dEntityExtCpuUtilOneMinute.description: This objects indicates the overall CPU busy percentage in the last 1 minute period. The value will be between 0% (idle) and 100% (very busy).

dEntityExtCpuUtilFiveMinutes.name: dEntityExtCpuUtilFiveMinutes
dEntityExtCpuUtilFiveMinutes.description: This objects indicates the overall CPU busy percentage in the last 5 minute period. The value will be between 0% (idle) and 100% (very busy).

dEntityExtVersionTable.name: dEntityExtVersionTable
dEntityExtVersionTable.description: The table is used to display version information of units.

dEntityExtVersionEntry.name: dEntityExtVersionEntry
dEntityExtVersionEntry.description: An entry contains version information of a unit.

dEntityExtVersionUnitId.name: dEntityExtVersionUnitId
dEntityExtVersionUnitId.description: This object indicates the unit (stacking device) or slot (chassis device) ID.

dEntityExtVersionBootloader.name: dEntityExtVersionBootloader
dEntityExtVersionBootloader.description: This object indicates the bootloader version of the unit.

dEntityExtVersionRuntime.name: dEntityExtVersionRuntime
dEntityExtVersionRuntime.description: This object indicates the firmware version of one unit.

dEntityExtFanStatusChg.name: dEntityExtFanStatusChg
dEntityExtFanStatusChg.description: This trap indicates a fan fails (dEntityExtEnvFanStatus is 'fault') or recovers (dEntityExtEnvFanStatus is 'ok').

dEntityExtThermalStatusChg.name: dEntityExtThermalStatusChg
dEntityExtThermalStatusChg.description: This trap indicates a thermal alarms (dEntityExtEnvTempStatus is 'abnormal') or recovers (dEntityExtEnvTempStatus is 'ok').

dEntityExtPowerStatusChg.name: dEntityExtPowerStatusChg
dEntityExtPowerStatusChg.description: This trap indicates a power module fails, recovers or is removed.

dEntityExtAirFlowChg.name: dEntityExtAirFlowChg
dEntityExtAirFlowChg.description: This trap is triggered when the air flow status is changed from 'ok' to 'abnormal' and vice versa. dEntityExtEnvAirFlowStatus indicates the current (new) fan air flow state.

dEntityExtFactoryResetButton.name: dEntityExtFactoryResetButton
dEntityExtFactoryResetButton.description: This trap is triggered when the factory reset button was pressed.

dEntityExtCompliance.name: dEntityExtCompliance
dEntityExtCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the DLINKSW-ENTITY-EXT-MIB.

dEntityExtTempGroup.name: dEntityExtTempGroup
dEntityExtTempGroup.description: A collection of objects provides information of the system temperature.

dEntityExtFanGroup.name: dEntityExtFanGroup
dEntityExtFanGroup.description: A collection of objects providing informations of fans.

dEntityExtPowerGroup.name: dEntityExtPowerGroup
dEntityExtPowerGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information of power modules.

dEntityExtSystemInfoGroup.name: dEntityExtSystemInfoGroup
dEntityExtSystemInfoGroup.description: A collection of objects provides information of the system temperature.

dEntityExtGenericNotifInfoGroup.name: dEntityExtGenericNotifInfoGroup
dEntityExtGenericNotifInfoGroup.description: A collection of objects provides generic information for binding variables of notification.

dEntityExtFanNotifGroup.name: dEntityExtFanNotifGroup
dEntityExtFanNotifGroup.description: A collection of notifications for indicating the status change of fans.

dEntityExtThermalNotifGroup.name: dEntityExtThermalNotifGroup
dEntityExtThermalNotifGroup.description: A collection of notifications for indicating the status change of thermals.

dEntityExtPowerNotifGroup.name: dEntityExtPowerNotifGroup
dEntityExtPowerNotifGroup.description: A collection of notifications for indicating the status change of power module.

dEntityExtAirFlowNotifGroup.name: dEntityExtAirFlowNotifGroup
dEntityExtAirFlowNotifGroup.description: A collection of notifications for indicating the status change of the air flow.

dEntityExtFactoryResetButtonNotifGroup.name: dEntityExtFactoryResetButtonNotifGroup
dEntityExtFactoryResetButtonNotifGroup.description: A collection of notifications for indicating the factory reset button.
